# Kudara, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Kudara (; , Kh√ºderi) is a rural locality (a selo) in Kabansky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 2,058 as of 2010. There are 21 streets.
Geography
Kudara is located 47&nbsp;km north of Kabansk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Korsakovo is the nearest rural locality.
